WEBVTT

00:00.501 --> 00:01.702
<i>Previously on</i>
<i>"The Rookie"...</i>

00:01.702 --> 00:02.970
That's Aaron Thorsen.

00:02.970 --> 00:04.471
Rich kid.
TikTok famous

00:04.471 --> 00:07.641
before he got arrested for
murdering his roommate in Paris.

00:07.641 --> 00:10.811
I was locked in a cell
for 541 days.

00:10.811 --> 00:13.313
The person who murdered Patrick,
he's still out there,

00:13.313 --> 00:15.148
and no one is looking for him

00:15.148 --> 00:16.483
because they still think
that I did it.

00:16.483 --> 00:18.519
I don't want to be a part of
this reality TV show.

00:18.519 --> 00:20.554
Sweetie, it's only
gonna help you.

00:20.554 --> 00:23.190
I'm Morris Mackey. I'm
the reality TV producer here.

00:23.190 --> 00:25.526
I just want to say,
this has been so fascinating.

00:25.526 --> 00:28.228
I love true crime,
and to be in a documentary,

00:28.228 --> 00:29.863
it's just --
it's a dream come true.

00:29.863 --> 00:30.864
Thank you.
Thank you.

00:30.864 --> 00:34.034
♪♪

00:34.034 --> 00:35.836
Nolan:
Do I just...?

00:36.837 --> 00:38.171
You're back.

00:38.171 --> 00:39.172
Interviewer:
Another crazy story --

00:39.172 --> 00:42.042
how could I stay away?
Thank you.

00:42.042 --> 00:43.544
You good to go?
Um, yeah.

00:43.544 --> 00:45.178
Where should I, uh --
where should I start?

00:45.178 --> 00:47.514
Why don't you, uh, tell me
about Aaron Thorsen?

00:47.514 --> 00:50.350
Well, Aaron came
to the F. T. O. program

00:50.350 --> 00:52.119
with the deck stacked
against him.

00:52.119 --> 00:55.222
He had to sue the LAPD
even to get into the Academy.

00:55.222 --> 00:57.391
I mean, you have to respect
just how hard he fought

00:57.391 --> 00:59.059
just to be here.

00:59.059 --> 01:03.230
Uh, but what happened in Paris
never left him,

01:03.230 --> 01:05.232
no matter how hard he tried
to move on.

01:05.232 --> 01:07.034
People would argue that doing
a reality show

01:07.034 --> 01:09.102
is the opposite
of moving on.

01:09.102 --> 01:10.938
Well, those people
haven't experienced

01:10.938 --> 01:12.706
what it's like
to be infamous.

01:12.706 --> 01:16.276
I mean, Aaron was desperate to
reset the way the world saw him.

01:16.276 --> 01:17.711
And it all blew up
in his face.

01:17.711 --> 01:20.547
Yeah.
Yeah, it really did.

01:20.547 --> 01:22.883
♪♪

01:22.883 --> 01:24.918
[ Gunshots ]

01:24.918 --> 01:27.654
[ People shouting ]

01:27.654 --> 01:28.755
[ Glass shatters ]

01:28.755 --> 01:30.757
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:30.757 --> 01:33.126
Aaron: I can't believe this
is happening to me again.

01:33.126 --> 01:34.428
Interviewer: It's nice
to see you again.

01:34.428 --> 01:35.462
Mm-hmm.

01:35.462 --> 01:37.598
And congratulations
on the baby.

01:37.598 --> 01:38.765
Thank you.

01:38.765 --> 01:40.434
Did being pregnant
make what you went through

01:40.434 --> 01:41.401
with Aaron
more stressful?

01:41.401 --> 01:42.936
Not here to talk about me.

01:42.936 --> 01:44.905
Fair enough. Uh,
let's talk about

01:44.905 --> 01:45.906
the reality show.

01:45.906 --> 01:48.241
Okay.
It was his mom's idea.

01:48.241 --> 01:50.577
It was a way to rebrand
his image.

01:50.577 --> 01:52.412
And what did you think
of the title?

01:53.413 --> 01:54.615
No comment.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.083
Seriously, though.
You have to have

01:56.083 --> 01:57.851
had an opinion --
Listen, you're not
gonna get me

01:57.851 --> 02:00.821
to say that dumbass title,
so let's just move on.

02:00.821 --> 02:03.824
[ Up-tempo hip-hop music plays ]

02:03.824 --> 02:13.800
♪♪

02:13.800 --> 02:14.768
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

02:14.768 --> 02:15.769
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

02:15.769 --> 02:18.005
[ Cell door closing ]

02:18.005 --> 02:19.006
[ Siren chirps ]

02:19.006 --> 02:24.111
♪♪

02:24.111 --> 02:25.946
[ Engine revving ]

02:25.946 --> 02:27.280
♪♪

02:27.280 --> 02:29.449
Yeah, so back there
is my parents' room

02:29.449 --> 02:30.784
and the family room.

02:30.784 --> 02:34.855
Um... Oh, right here,
this is my favorite photo.

02:34.855 --> 02:36.323
I was 6.

02:36.323 --> 02:37.824
And you might recognize
my dad.

02:37.824 --> 02:40.994
He was part of a '90s rap duo,
Flex n' Flow.

02:40.994 --> 02:42.162
That's them right here.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.330
[ Rapping ]
♪ Party's never stoppin' ♪

02:43.330 --> 02:44.498
♪ Who the boys
that make the noise? ♪

02:44.498 --> 02:45.666
♪ Flex n' Flow, yo,
Flex n' Flow ♪

02:45.666 --> 02:46.967
Yeah, man, when I was a kid,
I used to love

02:46.967 --> 02:49.469
riding my tricycle up and down
this hallway.

02:49.469 --> 02:52.139
Until he knocked over my Music
Industry Achievement Award

02:52.139 --> 02:53.373
and broke it.

02:53.373 --> 02:55.375
Aaron tried to put it back
together with Play-Doh,

02:55.375 --> 02:57.210
thinking we wouldn't notice.

02:57.210 --> 03:01.148
But that's my son, always trying
to get away with something.

03:02.315 --> 03:03.650
Not anymore.

03:03.650 --> 03:06.853
I mean, now he's...
very responsible.

03:06.853 --> 03:08.355
♪♪

03:08.355 --> 03:10.724
Over here, we got
my childhood bedroom.

03:10.724 --> 03:13.427
[ Dog barking ]

03:13.427 --> 03:15.862
What the hell?

03:15.862 --> 03:18.532
Hey, I never had
this picture of Patrick.

03:18.532 --> 03:19.866
Did you put this here?

03:19.866 --> 03:21.835
Morris: We just thought it'd be
a nice surprise.

03:21.835 --> 03:23.236
Man, Morris, what the hell
did I tell you, man,

03:23.236 --> 03:24.671
about faking stuff like this?

03:24.671 --> 03:27.007
Relax.
Uh, not a big deal.

03:27.007 --> 03:28.709
We just wanted to do it
for a take.

03:28.709 --> 03:29.843
Yeah, man,
that's not cool.

03:29.843 --> 03:30.877
You know what?
You're right.

03:30.877 --> 03:32.045
My bad.

03:32.045 --> 03:35.048
We'll -- We'll do it again,
but without the photo.

03:35.048 --> 03:36.349
Okay.

03:36.349 --> 03:38.385
Yeah, okay.

03:41.288 --> 03:43.056
Got that?

03:43.056 --> 03:44.891
Morris was white-hot
from doing

03:44.891 --> 03:47.094
several award-winning
documentaries in a row.

03:47.094 --> 03:49.229
The king of those
"30 Under 30" lists.

03:49.229 --> 03:51.064
He had a real gift
for earning people's trust,

03:51.064 --> 03:53.400
convincing them
that he was on their side,

03:53.400 --> 03:55.736
that they have a say
on the final cut.

03:55.736 --> 03:57.904
Then -- surprise --
they didn't.

03:57.904 --> 04:00.907
[ Baby cooing ]

04:00.907 --> 04:02.209
Hey.

04:02.209 --> 04:05.045
Sorry. I, uh, totally forgot
this was happening today.

04:05.045 --> 04:06.246
We just started.

04:06.246 --> 04:07.714
Uh, don't forget to tell him
about the, uh,

04:07.714 --> 04:08.749
forensics expert.

04:08.749 --> 04:09.750
I know.

04:09.750 --> 04:11.585
And the, uh --
the French prosecutor.

04:11.585 --> 04:12.786
I sent you that interview,
right?

04:12.786 --> 04:14.755
He was biased against Aaron
from the jump.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.091
I'm a decade older,

04:18.091 --> 04:20.260
but Aaron and I
had similar upbringings --

04:20.260 --> 04:21.995
rich parents,
private schools.

04:21.995 --> 04:24.598
I'm just lucky social media
didn't exist.

04:24.598 --> 04:25.966
Look, if I was
in Aaron's generation,

04:25.966 --> 04:28.401
I would have just as much
embarrassing footage as he did.

04:28.401 --> 04:31.638
Of what?
You studying tort reform at 15?

04:31.638 --> 04:33.406
I got into trouble.

04:33.406 --> 04:34.775
Uh-huh.
Okay.

04:34.775 --> 04:36.777
The point is, when you grow up
in this world,

04:36.777 --> 04:39.412
you don't hear "no" a lot,
which can make you a real ass--

04:39.412 --> 04:41.148
can make you
a very selfish person.

04:41.148 --> 04:42.415
♪ Another day ♪

04:42.415 --> 04:43.917
Aaron: Ooh-hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

04:43.917 --> 04:45.652
Yo, they only got,
like, five pairs of these

04:45.652 --> 04:47.487
in the whole world,
and I got a pair.

04:47.487 --> 04:48.955
You don't have a pair,
but I do.

04:48.955 --> 04:50.690
What's up, what's up?!

04:50.690 --> 04:51.691
Hey, yo, what up,
everybody?

04:51.691 --> 04:52.826
It's your boy, AT!

04:52.826 --> 04:54.461
My guy Patty P right here.

04:54.461 --> 04:57.798
We got a pool party tonight.
Everybody come through.

04:57.798 --> 04:59.466
Got the matching,
you know?

04:59.466 --> 05:00.967
Got the matching.
And the shoes.

05:00.967 --> 05:02.435
Hey.
Have fun.

05:02.435 --> 05:04.104
You know what it is.
Hey! Whoa!

05:04.104 --> 05:05.672
[ Laughs ]
You know the vibes.

05:05.672 --> 05:06.673
You know the vibes!

05:06.673 --> 05:09.676
[ Cheering, laughter ]

05:09.676 --> 05:11.778
♪♪

05:11.778 --> 05:14.014
$30,000 a bottle,

05:14.014 --> 05:15.448
and he didn't drink a sip.

05:15.448 --> 05:17.818
That boy lost his mind.

05:17.818 --> 05:19.519
I had to get him out
of his comfort zone.

05:19.519 --> 05:21.988
I mean, I-I thought, you know,
a semester abroad

05:21.988 --> 05:23.323
would've helped him mature,

05:23.323 --> 05:25.826
so I sent him to Paris.

05:25.826 --> 05:30.330
♪♪

05:30.330 --> 05:31.832
<i>[ Clears throat ]</i>

05:31.832 --> 05:33.567
<i>I was on scholarship.</i>

05:33.567 --> 05:35.035
University of Michigan.

05:35.035 --> 05:36.636
Go Wolverines.
[ Chuckles ]

05:36.636 --> 05:38.538
I don't know why I said that.
Can I please start over?

05:38.538 --> 05:40.974
Interviewer: [ Laughs ]
You're doing fine.

05:40.974 --> 05:42.809
Uh, when did you first meet
Aaron and Patrick?

05:42.809 --> 05:45.345
The program held a mixer
when we first arrived.

05:45.345 --> 05:47.647
It was mostly just a bunch of
awkward college students

05:47.647 --> 05:49.049
butchering French,

05:49.049 --> 05:51.918
but Aaron and Patrick were from
this whole other world.

05:51.918 --> 05:53.887
First impressions?
[ Chuckles ]

05:53.887 --> 05:58.225
I mean, honestly, they seemed
like entitled douchebags.

05:58.225 --> 05:59.359
But then I got to know them.

05:59.359 --> 06:01.228
You know,
it was like another planet --

06:01.228 --> 06:02.762
Planet Rich.
[ Chuckles ]

06:02.762 --> 06:04.197
Patrick was the funniest.

06:04.197 --> 06:06.233
All that stuff you saw
on Instagram,

06:06.233 --> 06:07.601
no, that's not who they were.

06:07.601 --> 06:09.870
Yeah, I mean, we went from
the Two Musketeers to Four,

06:09.870 --> 06:11.171
you know, just like that.

06:11.171 --> 06:13.173
Me, Patrick,
Rowan, and Everest,

06:13.173 --> 06:17.010
we were, uh, inseparable.

06:17.010 --> 06:19.212
And uh...

06:19.212 --> 06:21.381
Man, that feels like
so long ago.

06:21.381 --> 06:22.716
Are you nervous about
the reunion?

06:22.716 --> 06:23.884
A little.

06:23.884 --> 06:25.919
Or a lot.

06:25.919 --> 06:29.623
Yeah, I mean, um, I haven't seen
them since the trial.

06:29.623 --> 06:32.726
And they all went home,
graduated from college,

06:32.726 --> 06:34.794
got jobs, and...

06:34.794 --> 06:35.929
I went to prison.

06:35.929 --> 06:37.397
Do they believe
in your innocence?

06:37.397 --> 06:39.232
Yeah, 100%.

06:39.232 --> 06:40.267
They've both said that.

06:40.267 --> 06:41.434
You know, there can be
a big difference

06:41.434 --> 06:44.437
between what people say
and what they believe.

06:44.437 --> 06:47.874
♪♪

06:47.874 --> 06:49.042
Sorry. Let's --
Hold on.

06:49.042 --> 06:51.244
Let me reset that.

06:51.244 --> 06:57.751
Sorry.
[ Breathes deeply ]

07:00.987 --> 07:03.256
Ro, Ro,
good to see you, man!

07:03.256 --> 07:04.257
Yeah, you too, man.

07:04.257 --> 07:05.659
Yeah.
You look so different.

07:05.659 --> 07:07.093
Yeah, I'm a little older.

07:07.093 --> 07:09.129
No, it's not that.
I don't know.

07:09.129 --> 07:10.463
You're like
a different guy.

07:10.463 --> 07:12.432
Something like that.
[ Chuckles ]

07:12.432 --> 07:13.667
I think I'm gonna cry.
Hey.

07:13.667 --> 07:15.568
No, no, no crying.
You're gonna mess up my makeup.

07:15.568 --> 07:16.569
Oh!

07:16.569 --> 07:18.405
Oh, I'm sorry
I didn't come sooner.

07:18.405 --> 07:19.906
No, d-- don't worry about it,
really.

07:19.906 --> 07:22.409
I'm just glad
to see you guys.

07:22.409 --> 07:24.144
Alright, so let's,
uh, get inside.

07:24.144 --> 07:26.413
I got food, drinks...

07:26.413 --> 07:29.082
cameras, and, uh...

07:29.082 --> 07:30.750
I'm sorry.
This is so weird.

07:30.750 --> 07:32.452
Hey, it's fine. We're just happy
to see you, bro.

07:33.353 --> 07:34.521
Yeah, me too.
Yeah.

07:34.521 --> 07:36.022
Yeah. Alright.
[ Camera chirps ]

07:36.022 --> 07:37.524
Connor: Guys, I got to swap out
my battery.

07:37.524 --> 07:38.959
Give me a second?

07:38.959 --> 07:40.627
Aaron: Okay.

07:48.268 --> 07:49.469
What the hell?

07:49.469 --> 07:59.279
[ Dramatic music plays ]

07:59.279 --> 08:00.780
Holy --
[ Video cuts ]

08:00.780 --> 08:02.449
Morris Mackey's throat
had been cut.

08:02.449 --> 08:03.783
By the time
his body was found,

08:03.783 --> 08:05.819
he'd been dead approximately
four hours.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.654
Interviewer: And who were
your initial suspects?

08:07.654 --> 08:09.489
Everyone who stepped foot
in the house that day.

08:09.489 --> 08:10.490
Including Aaron.

08:10.490 --> 08:11.825
Everyone.

08:11.825 --> 08:14.527
Interviewer: Good morning.
Good morning.

08:14.527 --> 08:15.528
It's nice to see you again.

08:15.528 --> 08:17.163
Nice to see you!

08:17.163 --> 08:18.164
I heard you were happy
with how

08:18.164 --> 08:19.332
the last documentary
came out.

08:19.332 --> 08:22.002
Oh, my God.
It was so good, and -- and --

08:22.002 --> 08:24.471
[ Laughs ]
And I got so many compliments.

08:24.471 --> 08:27.640
Oh, that's great.
How about you?

08:27.640 --> 08:29.642
Didn't see it.
Can we get started?

08:29.642 --> 08:30.977
Uh, yeah.

08:30.977 --> 08:33.346
So, tell me what happened when
you arrived at the scene.

08:33.346 --> 08:34.481
We were
the first responders.

08:34.481 --> 08:37.484
[ Siren wails ]

08:41.855 --> 08:43.023
Lucy: Whoa.

08:43.023 --> 08:44.024
Okay.

08:44.024 --> 08:46.192
It was a...frenetic day.

08:46.192 --> 08:50.530
So many people -- so --
so many personalities.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.866
But when you're talking
a star-studded crime scene

08:52.866 --> 08:56.336
with a witness list comprised
mostly of influencers,

08:56.336 --> 08:57.904
I guess that's
no surprise.

08:57.904 --> 08:59.539
Alright, look,
even with all those cameras

08:59.539 --> 09:01.841
and phones rolling in the house,
none of them caught anything

09:01.841 --> 09:03.843
even remotely helpful
to our investigation.

09:03.843 --> 09:05.211
Yeah. Luck?

09:05.211 --> 09:08.181
It just wasn't in our cards
that day.

09:09.349 --> 09:10.583
What?
Why are you so happy?

09:10.583 --> 09:12.886
I am being colorful.

09:12.886 --> 09:13.887
They will use more
of our coverage

09:13.887 --> 09:15.422
if we give them evocative
sound bites.

09:15.422 --> 09:16.756
I'm right, right?

09:16.756 --> 09:18.725
Can we get back
to the murder?

09:18.725 --> 09:20.960
I followed protocols.
You know, I -- I called it in,

09:20.960 --> 09:22.762
cleared the house,
did everything right.

09:22.762 --> 09:24.431
Lucy: Mm-hmm.
You believe me, right?

09:24.431 --> 09:25.632
O-Of course.

09:25.632 --> 09:27.600
I mean, but we have to
follow protocol, too.

09:27.600 --> 09:29.035
It's gonna be okay.

09:29.035 --> 09:30.904
I can't believe this
is happening to me again.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.038
I know.

09:32.038 --> 09:33.239
[ Breathing raggedly ]

09:33.239 --> 09:36.109
A-Are you okay?

09:36.109 --> 09:37.744
I think I'm having, like,
a panic attack.

09:37.744 --> 09:39.446
Oh, okay.
Uh, just sit down,

09:39.446 --> 09:40.780
and I'm gonna grab you
some water, okay?

09:40.780 --> 09:42.048
I'll be right back.

09:42.048 --> 09:43.550
Show's over.
Time to go.

09:43.550 --> 09:46.419
What? Uh, no, no, no.
No, it's not.

09:46.419 --> 09:48.421
This is my house,
my production.

09:48.421 --> 09:49.422
The show goes on.

09:49.422 --> 09:50.590
Connor, keep filming.

09:50.590 --> 09:51.791
Yeah, that's not
how this works.

09:51.791 --> 09:52.926
This is
my crime scene.

09:52.926 --> 09:55.428
Shut it off now.

09:55.428 --> 09:56.763
Shut it off!

09:56.763 --> 09:58.765
[ Camera beeps ]

09:58.765 --> 10:00.100
There was nothing
we could do.

10:00.100 --> 10:01.401
Tim:
Well, thanks for coming out.

10:01.401 --> 10:02.435
Yeah.

10:02.435 --> 10:04.737
Our paramedic crew was
short-staffed,

10:04.737 --> 10:08.241
and since we're all EMT-trained,
I was subbing in.

10:08.241 --> 10:09.275
Interviewer:
Oh, I don't understand.

10:09.275 --> 10:10.443
Why were you called in
at all?

10:10.443 --> 10:11.978
He was clearly dead,
right?

10:11.978 --> 10:14.481
You have no idea how many people
I see look that way

10:14.481 --> 10:16.249
and then spring back to life.

10:16.249 --> 10:17.750
Oh. Interesting.

10:17.750 --> 10:18.952
And what did you think
at the time?

10:18.952 --> 10:20.620
Did it seem to you
like Aaron did it?

10:20.620 --> 10:23.456
Of course not. He would never do
anything like that.

10:23.456 --> 10:25.525
Really? And you're confident
saying that --

10:25.525 --> 10:28.294
considering
your ex-husband?

10:28.294 --> 10:31.631
Wow. Okay.

10:31.631 --> 10:33.299
Ah, clearly,
you come prepared.

10:33.299 --> 10:38.004
Yeah, um, I --
I married a sociopath once.

10:38.004 --> 10:41.274
So maybe I'm not
the best judge of character.

10:41.274 --> 10:42.775
It's not about being
a good judge of character.

10:42.775 --> 10:44.177
We judge by the facts.

10:44.177 --> 10:45.812
Interviewer:
And what did the facts say?

10:45.812 --> 10:47.780
At first?

10:47.780 --> 10:48.982
Not much.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.719
How long you been here
filming today?

10:52.719 --> 10:54.487
About three
or four hours.

10:54.487 --> 10:55.655
After rehearsal
this morning,

10:55.655 --> 10:57.157
they had Everest and me
in the kitchen,

10:57.157 --> 10:58.525
getting our hair
and makeup done

10:58.525 --> 10:59.993
while they filmed
other stuff.

10:59.993 --> 11:01.494
Lucy: So you were in the kitchen
the whole time?

11:01.494 --> 11:05.231
Uh, well, I did sneak off
to crafty once or...

11:05.231 --> 11:06.666
four times.
I heard they had ice cream,

11:06.666 --> 11:07.834
and I've been dieting
like crazy

11:07.834 --> 11:08.968
'cause I was gonna be
on television,

11:08.968 --> 11:10.837
and I heard the camera
adds like 10 pounds.

11:10.837 --> 11:12.138
Is that true?

11:12.138 --> 11:13.806
Tim: So when was the last time
you saw Morris?

11:13.806 --> 11:15.875
Honestly, I ain't seen him
all day.

11:15.875 --> 11:17.143
I was dealing with work stuff

11:17.143 --> 11:18.811
right up
until we started filming.

11:18.811 --> 11:20.980
Lucy: And where were you
when Morris's body was found?

11:20.980 --> 11:22.815
In my office.

11:22.815 --> 11:24.150
And how would
you characterize

11:24.150 --> 11:26.352
Aaron's relationship
with Morris?

11:26.352 --> 11:28.354
[ Sighs ]

11:29.355 --> 11:31.224
It's important
you tell the truth.

11:33.026 --> 11:35.528
They didn't always agree about
the direction of the show.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.530
But my son,
he would never hurt anyone.

11:44.537 --> 11:47.407
Hey, do we really have
to do this in here?

11:47.407 --> 11:49.008
Yes, we do, son.

11:50.677 --> 11:53.680
Per government code 3300
and per Lybarger,

11:53.680 --> 11:56.216
I am required to advise
that you do <i>not</i> have

11:56.216 --> 11:57.750
the right
to remain silent.

11:57.750 --> 12:00.553
Anything you say can
and will be used against you.

12:00.553 --> 12:03.389
Refusal to fully
and completely answer

12:03.389 --> 12:06.125
all of Detective Lopez's
questions

12:06.125 --> 12:09.729
will result
in immediate termination.

12:09.729 --> 12:12.799
Do you understand?

12:12.799 --> 12:13.733
Yes, sir.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.101
And I'm here
to protect you

12:15.101 --> 12:16.903
as your union representative.

12:16.903 --> 12:18.538
This is your choice.

12:18.538 --> 12:20.273
But like
Sergeant Grey said,

12:20.273 --> 12:22.875
if you choose not to cooperate,
you will lose your job.

12:22.875 --> 12:24.210
Of course I'll cooperate.

12:26.212 --> 12:27.380
Good man.

12:29.582 --> 12:30.783
Alright.

12:30.783 --> 12:32.085
I'll leave you to it.

12:33.753 --> 12:35.788
[ Sighs ]

12:35.788 --> 12:36.956
I didn't kill Morris.

12:36.956 --> 12:38.258
[ Door closes ]

12:40.927 --> 12:45.098
When I saw him lying there,
like Patrick...

12:45.098 --> 12:46.332
Lopez: I understand.

12:46.332 --> 12:48.234
But it was common knowledge
that you and Morris

12:48.234 --> 12:49.902
weren't on
the best of terms.

12:49.902 --> 12:52.972
Who are you with? TMZ?

12:52.972 --> 12:54.407
You still feeding off my grief,
you vultures?!
Come on, guys.

12:54.407 --> 12:55.908
Morris,
what are you doing, man?
Get 'em out of here, man!

12:55.908 --> 12:57.644
Get out of here now!
Go!

12:57.644 --> 12:59.912
Yeah, what he did
to Patrick's dad

12:59.912 --> 13:03.449
was callous and exploitative,

13:03.449 --> 13:05.351
but I wouldn't kill him
for it.

13:05.351 --> 13:06.786
Harper: Yeah, that was bad.

13:06.786 --> 13:10.323
Aaron pulled over Patrick's dad
in a routine car stop.

13:10.323 --> 13:12.792
It was
a total random reunion,

13:12.792 --> 13:16.296
but Morris and his cameraman
were there filming,

13:16.296 --> 13:18.631
and that just made
everything worse.

13:18.631 --> 13:21.934
Dexter Hayes, he was a --
a grieving father, you know?

13:21.934 --> 13:26.105
And he -- he took a swing
at Officer Thorsen,

13:26.105 --> 13:27.106
so we had to book him,

13:27.106 --> 13:30.276
but we let him go
as soon as we could.

13:30.276 --> 13:32.512
And, you know, I thought
that would be the end of it.

13:32.512 --> 13:33.946
Interviewer: But you suspected
that Patrick's dad

13:33.946 --> 13:35.948
could have killed Morris?
We did.

13:35.948 --> 13:39.152
He was furious
about "Every Rose Has A --"

13:39.152 --> 13:41.154
about the reality show.

13:41.154 --> 13:44.824
And after years of the press
feeding off of his grief,

13:44.824 --> 13:47.727
yeah, it was believable
that he could've snapped.

13:47.727 --> 13:49.862
This is absurd.
You do know that?

13:49.862 --> 13:50.997
Tim: Alright, sir,
can you tell me where you were

13:50.997 --> 13:52.332
yesterday afternoon?

13:52.332 --> 13:54.967
I was in the office,
morning to midnight.

13:54.967 --> 13:56.969
Ask any one
of my employees.

13:56.969 --> 13:58.538
I didn't do this.

13:58.538 --> 14:00.540
Any idea who did?

14:00.540 --> 14:03.543
I can tell you that
whoever killed that man,

14:03.543 --> 14:06.646
his last name is Thorsen.

14:06.646 --> 14:09.716
I blame myself for ever letting
them into Patrick's life.

14:09.716 --> 14:10.850
They're a sick family.

14:10.850 --> 14:13.419
And Aaron is not
the only killer among them.

14:13.419 --> 14:14.687
Interviewer:
What did he mean by that?

14:14.687 --> 14:15.855
You know
what he meant by that.

14:15.855 --> 14:18.358
And we knew
from the reality show

14:18.358 --> 14:20.860
that Morris gave
Aaron's father a clear motive.

14:20.860 --> 14:23.696
And that's what I was thinking
for the opening theme.

14:23.696 --> 14:24.697
Yeah?
Yeah.

14:24.697 --> 14:25.531
I like it.

14:25.531 --> 14:26.699
You do?

14:26.699 --> 14:28.568
Almost as much
as I like you.

14:28.568 --> 14:30.002
Mm.

14:30.002 --> 14:32.004
You're so sweet.
[ Door opens ]

14:32.004 --> 14:33.339
Oh.

14:33.339 --> 14:34.507
Lincoln: Hey!

14:34.507 --> 14:36.542
You hooking up
with my wife, man?!

14:36.542 --> 14:37.844
Linc,
it's not what you think.

14:37.844 --> 14:40.380
Boy, you better get
the hell up out of here!

14:40.380 --> 14:41.714
[ Bottle shatters ]

14:43.182 --> 14:44.684
What the hell was that?!

14:44.684 --> 14:47.053
Are you seriously doing this
to me again?!

14:47.053 --> 14:48.421
In my own house!

14:48.421 --> 14:49.756
Interview: There's footage
of Lincoln catching

14:49.756 --> 14:51.724
Morris and Yvonne
in an intimate moment.

14:51.724 --> 14:54.060
That had to factor
into your investigation.

14:54.060 --> 14:56.295
Jealousy is
a primal motive.

14:56.295 --> 14:57.597
And some believe
that Lincoln had killed

14:57.597 --> 14:59.232
for jealousy
once before.

14:59.232 --> 15:01.567
He was a suspect in
a 20-year-old murder, wasn't he?

15:01.567 --> 15:02.568
Yes, he was.

15:02.568 --> 15:04.036
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

15:04.036 --> 15:05.037
[ Gunshots ]

15:09.275 --> 15:11.878
Interviewer: What can you
tell me about your father's
hip-hop duo, Flex n' Flow?

15:11.878 --> 15:12.712
I mean, I was, like, a baby,
you know,

15:12.712 --> 15:14.113
when they were
at their height.

15:14.113 --> 15:17.383
And, uh, that was the year
"Make Da Noise" went platinum.

15:17.383 --> 15:18.418
Interviewer: Flex n' Flow
had one of the most

15:18.418 --> 15:19.819
iconic singles
of the late '90s.

15:19.819 --> 15:21.320
Oh, my God.
"Make Da Noise"?

15:21.320 --> 15:24.424
That's like one
of my go-to karaoke jams.

15:24.424 --> 15:25.925
[ Rapping ] ♪ My crib,
it's all a-poppin' ♪

15:25.925 --> 15:27.260
♪ The party's
never stoppin' ♪

15:27.260 --> 15:28.327
♪ Who da boyz that
make da noise? ♪

15:28.327 --> 15:30.463
♪ Flex 'n Flow, yo,
Flex n' Flow ♪

15:30.463 --> 15:31.664
Can I be interviewed
alone?

15:31.664 --> 15:33.599
[ Record scratching ]

15:33.599 --> 15:34.934
Yeah, we comin' for you.

15:34.934 --> 15:35.935
[ Rapping ] ♪ My crib,
it's all a-poppin' ♪

15:35.935 --> 15:37.403
♪ This party's
never stoppin' ♪

15:37.403 --> 15:38.471
♪ We're the boyz
who make da noise ♪

15:38.471 --> 15:39.939
♪ Flex n' Flow, yo,
Flex n' Flow ♪

15:39.939 --> 15:41.307
♪ My crib,
it's all a-poppin' ♪

15:41.307 --> 15:42.642
♪ This party's
never stoppin' ♪

15:42.642 --> 15:43.776
♪ We're the boyz
who make da noise ♪

15:43.776 --> 15:45.144
♪ Flex n' Flow, yo,
Flex n' Flow ♪

15:45.144 --> 15:46.245
♪ Flex n' Flow ♪

15:46.245 --> 15:53.986
♪♪

15:53.986 --> 15:55.455
[ Chuckles ]

15:55.455 --> 15:57.790
Oh, yes, that's me.

15:57.790 --> 16:00.159
I was a Flow Girl.

16:00.159 --> 16:01.794
[ Chuckles ]
Wait. What?

16:01.794 --> 16:04.630
There was a scout who saw me
cheering in high school,

16:04.630 --> 16:06.466
and he asked me to audition.

16:06.466 --> 16:08.634
At first, I thought he was
just trying to get in my pants.

16:08.634 --> 16:14.106
But it turned out to be legit,
and it was for Flex n' Flow.

16:14.106 --> 16:16.142
I was the biggest fan.

16:16.142 --> 16:17.310
Interviewer: What are you
wearing, by the way?

16:17.310 --> 16:20.847
Oh, I teach capoeira
on Thursdays and Sundays.

16:20.847 --> 16:21.981
Oh.

16:21.981 --> 16:23.616
Did you ever see
Flex n' Flow argue

16:23.616 --> 16:24.517
while you were working
with them?

16:24.517 --> 16:27.320
Mm, I mean...well, sure,

16:27.320 --> 16:28.988
but nothing serious.

16:28.988 --> 16:31.157
They were like brothers,
and brothers fight.

16:31.157 --> 16:32.492
What do you say to the people
who are convinced

16:32.492 --> 16:34.360
that your husband
killed his late partner?

16:34.360 --> 16:37.163
Oh, honey, this alleged "feud"
between Linc and Calvin

16:37.163 --> 16:40.333
has gotten blown way out
of proportion over the years.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.001
But what about the night
of Calvin's murder?

16:42.001 --> 16:44.337
The infamous pre-release party
for "2 Hype Homies"?

16:44.337 --> 16:46.873
Did the party
get a little wild? Sure.

16:46.873 --> 16:49.308
Did the police come
and break it up? Mm-hmm.

16:49.308 --> 16:51.878
And did Linc and Calvin argue?
You bet.

16:51.878 --> 16:53.980
But they were just
passionate people.

16:53.980 --> 16:57.316
And nobody
ever threatened nobody.

16:57.316 --> 17:00.686
Yeah, they, uh --
they threatened each other.

17:00.686 --> 17:01.687
I was there.

17:01.687 --> 17:03.356
I was a rookie officer then.

17:03.356 --> 17:06.192
And my T. O. and I had got
a 415 call

17:06.192 --> 17:08.561
for an out-of-control party.

17:08.561 --> 17:12.532
It was a record release event
for Flex n' Flow.

17:12.532 --> 17:15.034
But anyway,
as we were breaking things up,

17:15.034 --> 17:17.336
I saw Flex n' Flow
in each other's faces.

17:17.336 --> 17:18.871
Interviewer: Could you hear
what they were fighting about?

17:18.871 --> 17:22.508
No. Um, as I approached,
their limousine was pulling up.

17:22.508 --> 17:24.010
But Flex -- um --

17:24.010 --> 17:26.679
um, I'm sorry, Lincoln --
was still very hot.

17:26.679 --> 17:31.417
He refused to get into the limo
with Flow, and, um...

17:31.417 --> 17:33.886
Yeah, he said
that he'd rather walk

17:33.886 --> 17:36.255
than to deal
with Flow's nonsense.

17:36.255 --> 17:37.723
Um...

17:37.723 --> 17:39.292
It was a good thing, too.

17:39.292 --> 17:41.727
Anchor: A devastating loss
for the music industry today,

17:41.727 --> 17:45.731
as Calvin Yard, one half
of the popular duo Flex n' Flow,

17:45.731 --> 17:48.200
was gunned down in Los Angeles
last night

17:48.200 --> 17:50.570
after leaving
his record launch party.

17:50.570 --> 17:52.538
It couldn't have been
more than five minutes later

17:52.538 --> 17:54.941
that we got
a shots-fired call.

17:54.941 --> 17:59.545
As Flow's limo was making
the turn on La Cienega,

17:59.545 --> 18:02.915
a car pulled alongside it
and unloaded 20 rounds

18:02.915 --> 18:04.383
at the rear of the vehicle.

18:04.383 --> 18:05.918
[ Gunshots ]

18:05.918 --> 18:08.588
Um, Flow was shot
seven times.

18:09.922 --> 18:12.158
Yeah.

18:12.158 --> 18:14.327
That was my first homicide.

18:14.327 --> 18:15.928
I'll never forget it.

18:15.928 --> 18:17.663
It changes you.

18:17.663 --> 18:21.934
I did not have anything to do
with Calvin's death.

18:21.934 --> 18:23.736
Interviewer: But at the time of
his murder, all the talk was --

18:23.736 --> 18:24.937
That was garbage, man.

18:24.937 --> 18:26.138
All garbage.

18:26.138 --> 18:27.473
I loved Calvin
like a brother.

18:27.473 --> 18:29.275
You know, this --

18:29.275 --> 18:30.743
this is
straight-up exploitive.

18:30.743 --> 18:33.746
Calvin's murder was solved
decades ago, and you know it.

18:33.746 --> 18:37.249
A man named Gary Brown
was convicted of Flow's murder.

18:37.249 --> 18:39.652
It turns out Flow
was sleeping with Gary's wife.

18:39.652 --> 18:43.289
So as far as the LAPD
was concerned, case closed.

18:43.289 --> 18:45.625
Yeah, but the aura of guilt
haunted Lincoln's reputation

18:45.625 --> 18:47.860
like a dark shroud.

18:47.860 --> 18:48.961
I'm sorry.

18:48.961 --> 18:51.464
That was really good.

18:51.464 --> 18:53.165
Thanks.

18:53.165 --> 18:55.101
And with Lincoln alibi'd out,
you know,

18:55.101 --> 18:57.103
the investigation
focused on Yvonne.

18:57.103 --> 18:59.438
Mrs. Thorsen, how long
had you been having an affair

18:59.438 --> 19:00.339
with Morris Mackey?

19:00.339 --> 19:01.607
[ Scoffs ] Please.

19:01.607 --> 19:03.342
I was not sleeping
with him.

19:03.342 --> 19:05.778
But the footage -- from
"Every Rose Has A Thorsen" --

19:05.778 --> 19:08.447
we saw it.
That was for the show.

19:08.447 --> 19:10.282
What, are you saying
you staged it?

19:10.282 --> 19:13.519
It's a reality show.
Of course we staged it.

19:13.519 --> 19:15.554
I can prove it.
I have the rest of the footage.

19:15.554 --> 19:17.990
Boy, you better get
the hell up out of here!

19:17.990 --> 19:19.025
[ Bottle shatters ]

19:20.526 --> 19:22.161
What the hell was that?!

19:22.161 --> 19:24.397
Are you seriously doing this
to me again?!

19:24.397 --> 19:25.665
In my own house!

19:25.665 --> 19:27.667
You got some nerve!

19:27.667 --> 19:29.702
L-Let's talk about all the women
you slept with

19:29.702 --> 19:31.337
when you were F-Flex?

19:31.337 --> 19:33.339
Morris: Cut!

19:33.339 --> 19:35.341
Cut, cut, cut, cut.

19:35.341 --> 19:38.811
Linc, buddy,
you're going off-script.

19:38.811 --> 19:39.979
"I can't believe
you're seriously

19:39.979 --> 19:41.213
doing this to me <i>again"?</i>

19:41.213 --> 19:42.715
That's not the line.

19:42.715 --> 19:44.316
Yeah, man,
I was improv'ing a little.

19:44.316 --> 19:46.018
Yeah, maybe not do that,
okay?

19:46.018 --> 19:47.720
It's a lot more powerful
if this is the first time

19:47.720 --> 19:49.221
Yvonne has stepped out
on you.

19:49.221 --> 19:51.257
Okay.
So, Morris, how did I do?

19:51.257 --> 19:52.758
It was a bit big.

19:52.758 --> 19:54.894
Yeah, maybe, uh,
dial it back a hair.

19:54.894 --> 19:56.062
Let's go again.

19:56.062 --> 19:57.763
Man: <i>Back to one.</i>

19:57.763 --> 19:59.031
Go.

19:59.031 --> 20:00.032
We're making a show,
people.

20:00.032 --> 20:01.734
[ Clears throat ]

20:01.734 --> 20:04.670
None of that was in the footage
you turned over to us.

20:04.670 --> 20:06.172
Oops. My bad.

20:06.172 --> 20:08.507
We want everything --
now --

20:08.507 --> 20:10.676
or you'll be arrested
for obstruction.

20:10.676 --> 20:12.845
Ooh, that was good.

20:12.845 --> 20:15.014
Do you think I can get
a copy of that?

20:15.014 --> 20:17.016
That will play really well
in the show.

20:17.016 --> 20:18.617
Mrs. Thorsen,
this is serious.

20:18.617 --> 20:20.553
Morris Mackey was murdered
in your house.

20:20.553 --> 20:22.121
Your son
is still a suspect.

20:22.121 --> 20:24.223
Just like the police
to only focus

20:24.223 --> 20:26.292
on what's
in front of their nose.

20:26.292 --> 20:28.894
Morris Mackey didn't just appear
out of thin air

20:28.894 --> 20:30.429
when he started working
for me.

20:30.429 --> 20:32.898
Honey,
the man had enemies.

20:32.898 --> 20:38.204
[ Crowd chanting "We are Q!
We are Q!" ]

20:38.204 --> 20:39.772
They're the crazy ones!

20:39.772 --> 20:41.207
We're the sane ones!

20:41.207 --> 20:43.275
You're the cult!
You're sheep!

20:43.275 --> 20:45.411
Prior to working
with the Thorsen family,

20:45.411 --> 20:48.881
Morris had been hired by a bunch
of QAnon conspiracy theorists.

20:48.881 --> 20:51.050
Apparently, they didn't like
the negative publicity

20:51.050 --> 20:52.251
they were getting,

20:52.251 --> 20:54.286
and they wanted
to show their side.

20:54.286 --> 20:55.488
Try to control
the narrative.

20:55.488 --> 20:56.655
Mm.
Interviewer: So what happened?

20:56.655 --> 20:58.657
Morris was allowed
into the inner sanctum.

20:58.657 --> 21:01.427
Conducted dozens of interviews
with founders and followers.

21:01.427 --> 21:03.629
But he didn't make
a propaganda film,

21:03.629 --> 21:04.764
he told the truth.

21:04.764 --> 21:05.931
[ Modulated voice ]
We're in a war.

21:05.931 --> 21:07.933
Every one of us is prepared
to start killing

21:07.933 --> 21:08.801
for our freedom.

21:08.801 --> 21:09.902
Morris may have won
an Emmy,

21:09.902 --> 21:11.904
but he also pissed off
a lot of unhinged

21:11.904 --> 21:13.472
and hyper-violent people.

21:13.472 --> 21:15.141
The storm is coming.

21:15.141 --> 21:16.075
There will be retribution.

21:20.446 --> 21:23.249
Interviewer: I've heard rumors
that you have insight into
the QAnon angle on this case.

21:23.249 --> 21:25.618
Have you ever tried to put
toothpaste back in the tube?

21:25.618 --> 21:27.653
Look, I know
it's an expression,

21:27.653 --> 21:30.456
but have you actually tried
to do it?

21:30.456 --> 21:31.957
I have.

21:31.957 --> 21:33.626
It's basically impossible.

21:33.626 --> 21:35.361
And what do you think Q
is trying to tell people

21:35.361 --> 21:37.963
with his Q-Drops,
these cryptic messages?

21:37.963 --> 21:39.532
I really wasn't trying
to say anything.

21:39.532 --> 21:42.768
I was just typing, and maybe
I got a little carried away.

21:42.768 --> 21:44.336
Wait.
What did you say?

21:45.604 --> 21:49.275
Well, I guess now is as good
a time as any to reveal it.

21:51.610 --> 21:53.145
I'm Q.

21:53.145 --> 21:54.446
Smitty is Q?

21:54.446 --> 21:55.447
I'm sorry. What?

21:55.447 --> 21:57.116
Lord, give me strength.
What?

21:57.116 --> 21:59.652
A lot of writers
use pseudonyms.

21:59.652 --> 22:02.321
Q is my first initial,
so...

22:02.321 --> 22:04.023
Hey, is my name down there?

22:05.991 --> 22:06.992
But it was an accident?

22:06.992 --> 22:09.361
He -- He didn't start it
on purpose?

22:09.361 --> 22:10.496
Interviewer:
That's what he said.

22:10.496 --> 22:11.831
Yeah,
sounds like Smitty.

22:11.831 --> 22:13.999
I was trying to start
the fan-fiction club

22:13.999 --> 22:16.635
for "This Is Us,"
and things just got out of hand.

22:16.635 --> 22:18.304
Interviewer: What the hell
does "This is Us" fanfic

22:18.304 --> 22:19.505
have to do with a cult?

22:19.505 --> 22:22.675
I mistakenly mixed cough syrup
with diet pills

22:22.675 --> 22:25.644
when I was writing
this satanic, alien story line

22:25.644 --> 22:27.513
for Jack and Rebecca.

22:27.513 --> 22:30.382
I woke up the next morning
and read it --

22:30.382 --> 22:31.650
none of it made sense.

22:31.650 --> 22:34.186
But, overnight,
I'd gotten so many followers,

22:34.186 --> 22:35.354
I just went with it.

22:35.354 --> 22:37.923
You can't put the toothpaste
back in the tube.

22:39.391 --> 22:43.028
Morris had received threats from
hundreds of QAnon followers,

22:43.028 --> 22:45.598
but when we started
investigating them,

22:45.598 --> 22:47.700
one immediately stood out.

22:47.700 --> 22:49.034
Interviewer: Tell me
about Connor Hart.

22:49.034 --> 22:50.336
What about him
got your attention?

22:50.336 --> 22:53.172
Well, he was working as a
cameraman on the reality show,

22:53.172 --> 22:55.407
so -- that.

22:55.407 --> 22:56.508
[ Door opens ]

22:56.508 --> 22:59.178
Tim: Connor,
thanks for coming down.

22:59.178 --> 23:00.512
I'm not in trouble, am I?

23:00.512 --> 23:03.515
No. We just need to clear
a few things up.

23:03.515 --> 23:05.885
I told you
everything I know.

23:05.885 --> 23:09.221
I was getting a battery,
and he was just lying there.

23:09.221 --> 23:10.556
I'm not sure
if you're aware,

23:10.556 --> 23:13.225
but it's common to run
background checks on witnesses.

23:13.225 --> 23:14.793
And when we looked into you,
we discovered

23:14.793 --> 23:16.228
that you're a member
of QAnon.

23:16.228 --> 23:17.730
No, no, no, I --

23:17.730 --> 23:19.732
I may have gone
to a political rally or two,

23:19.732 --> 23:21.233
but I'm really
not into that.

23:21.233 --> 23:22.868
I swear.

23:22.868 --> 23:24.536
[ Manipulated voice ]
We're in a war.

23:24.536 --> 23:27.439
Every one of us is prepared to
start killing for our freedom.

23:27.439 --> 23:29.074
The storm is coming.

23:29.074 --> 23:30.709
There will be retribution.

23:30.709 --> 23:31.877
[ Video fast-forwarding ]

23:36.048 --> 23:38.550
So, clearly,
you are a follower of Q.

23:38.550 --> 23:39.952
Why would you work
for Morris?

23:39.952 --> 23:41.453
Honestly?

23:41.453 --> 23:42.788
I realized
Morris was the best thing

23:42.788 --> 23:44.590
that could have happened
to the movement.

23:44.590 --> 23:45.958
That makes no sense.

23:45.958 --> 23:47.626
But it does.

23:47.626 --> 23:50.629
Morris's documentary exposed
who was a true believer.

23:50.629 --> 23:52.932
And who wasn't.

23:52.932 --> 23:54.934
He never admitted it,

23:54.934 --> 23:57.970
but I think Morris
was working for Q.

23:57.970 --> 23:59.905
That's why I followed him
to the next gig.

23:59.905 --> 24:02.141
Do you still consider yourself
a believer of Q?

24:02.141 --> 24:05.244
Well, some stuff
didn't come true.

24:05.244 --> 24:07.413
The London bombing,
the Pope's arrest,

24:07.413 --> 24:08.747
Zuckerberg still has a job.

24:08.747 --> 24:10.749
January 20th
came and went,

24:10.749 --> 24:12.618
March 4th came and went.

24:12.618 --> 24:15.654
I'm starting to think Kennedy
is still dead.

24:15.654 --> 24:16.789
Both of them.

24:16.789 --> 24:17.790
Mm.

24:17.790 --> 24:20.993
So you don't believe
in Q anymore?

24:20.993 --> 24:22.795
Oh, I believe every word.

24:22.795 --> 24:24.196
Connor was, um --

24:24.196 --> 24:26.131
Deranged?

24:26.131 --> 24:28.467
Let's say...
reality-challenged,

24:28.467 --> 24:30.269
which doesn't make him
a killer.

24:30.269 --> 24:33.105
No. And the fact that he had
a camera on his shoulder

24:33.105 --> 24:35.007
for the entire
murder window

24:35.007 --> 24:37.009
means that he couldn't
have killed Morris,

24:37.009 --> 24:38.944
so we were back
to square one.

24:38.944 --> 24:40.779
Interviewer: When the QAnon lead
didn't pan out,

24:40.779 --> 24:42.648
how did you pick up
the pieces of the case?

24:42.648 --> 24:45.484
We rolled up our sleeves
and put in the hours.

24:45.484 --> 24:47.152
We took on
the painstaking process

24:47.152 --> 24:49.888
of reviewing
every piece of video Morris shot

24:49.888 --> 24:51.323
in the weeks
before he died,

24:51.323 --> 24:55.060
including the footage
Yvonne "forgot" to give us.

24:55.060 --> 24:57.162
Until I found something
that changed everything.

24:57.162 --> 24:59.832
♪♪

24:59.832 --> 25:01.867
Lopez!

25:01.867 --> 25:03.302
Come look at this!

25:03.302 --> 25:05.037
So I immediately informed
Detective Lopez

25:05.037 --> 25:06.005
of what I discovered.

25:06.005 --> 25:06.839
Look what I just found.

25:06.839 --> 25:08.173
Wow.

25:08.173 --> 25:09.174
What?

25:09.174 --> 25:11.143
Look.

25:11.143 --> 25:13.012
Morris: Okay.

25:14.646 --> 25:16.215
[ Sighs ]

25:18.384 --> 25:21.186
I thought I knew everything
about Patrick's murder.

25:21.186 --> 25:23.222
I had done my homework.

25:23.222 --> 25:27.860
But the truth was hiding right
in front of me all this time.

25:27.860 --> 25:31.030
I know
who killed Patrick Hayes.

25:31.030 --> 25:32.197
And I can prove it. I --

25:32.197 --> 25:35.067
[ Door opens,
footsteps approaching ]

25:35.067 --> 25:36.335
Uh, someone's here.

25:37.669 --> 25:38.670
More to follow.

25:38.670 --> 25:40.172
Nolan: That video
was recorded

25:40.172 --> 25:42.207
minutes before
Morris was murdered.

25:46.578 --> 25:48.680
Interviewer: I mean, Morris
claiming that he knew

25:48.680 --> 25:49.748
who the killer was
must've been energizing for you.

25:49.748 --> 25:50.682
Finally. A break
in your roommate's murder --

25:50.682 --> 25:53.385
No, he --
He wasn't my roommate.

25:53.385 --> 25:55.754
And I -- I hate when people
call him that --

25:55.754 --> 25:57.389
you know, like we found
each other

25:57.389 --> 25:59.725
on some French Craigslist
or something like that.

25:59.725 --> 26:00.959
Patrick was my best friend,

26:00.959 --> 26:02.461
from the time
that we were little kids.

26:02.461 --> 26:03.896
I mean, I was at his house
so often,

26:03.896 --> 26:05.764
his dad bought us
two of everything,

26:05.764 --> 26:07.066
you know, like siblings.

26:07.066 --> 26:08.634
Yeah,
Patrick was my brother.

26:08.634 --> 26:10.202
How did it feel to hear
that Morris thought

26:10.202 --> 26:11.870
he'd discovered
who killed Patrick?

26:11.870 --> 26:16.375
I mean, there had been
so many theories over the years.

26:16.375 --> 26:18.911
And so many people think
that they had it figured out.

26:18.911 --> 26:22.581
I -- I just never really
got my hopes up about it.

26:22.581 --> 26:24.383
This was different, though.
I mean, he made a break

26:24.383 --> 26:25.918
in the case
and died minutes later.

26:25.918 --> 26:27.653
You have to see
the connection.

26:27.653 --> 26:32.157
Well, uh, in the words
of Detective Harper --

26:32.157 --> 26:35.260
We look for facts,
not stories.

26:35.260 --> 26:37.096
Yeah, sure, but, I mean,
the timing --

26:37.096 --> 26:38.997
I mean, these murders
had to be related.

26:38.997 --> 26:41.600
Whoever killed Patrick
also killed Morris.

26:41.600 --> 26:42.968
Interviewer: Is it possible
Morris found out

26:42.968 --> 26:44.570
that Aaron was the killer
all along?

26:44.570 --> 26:46.238
Not a chance.
The Paris police

26:46.238 --> 26:49.608
never had a shred of evidence
against Aaron.

26:49.608 --> 26:51.410
They fumbled
the entire case.

26:51.410 --> 26:52.611
Right off the bat,
the paparazzi

26:52.611 --> 26:54.613
completely contaminated
the crime scene.

26:54.613 --> 26:56.415
[ Speaking French ]

26:56.415 --> 26:58.584
[ Siren wailing ]

26:58.584 --> 26:59.952
[ Police radio chatter ]

26:59.952 --> 27:01.553
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

27:01.553 --> 27:04.356
[ Speaking French ]

27:04.356 --> 27:05.791
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

27:05.791 --> 27:07.793
[ Speaking French ]

27:07.793 --> 27:09.661
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

27:11.530 --> 27:13.665
Interviewer: But Aaron's DNA
was all over the murder weapon.

27:13.665 --> 27:15.300
You mean the knife
the killer pulled

27:15.300 --> 27:17.669
from the kitchen block
on Aaron and Patrick's counter?

27:17.669 --> 27:20.339
What -- What do you want to bet
that if we went to your house,

27:20.339 --> 27:22.674
we'd find your DNA
all over your stuff, too?

27:22.674 --> 27:24.943
I mean -- [ Stammers ]

27:24.943 --> 27:26.278
Was that too mean?

27:26.278 --> 27:28.981
No, that actually
felt good.

27:28.981 --> 27:30.449
It was a dumb question.

27:30.449 --> 27:32.151
From the beginning,
the French police's case

27:32.151 --> 27:33.652
against Aaron
seemed flawed --

27:33.652 --> 27:35.654
Oh, yeah.
Their case was a mess --

27:35.654 --> 27:38.056
and their forensics
were compromised.

27:38.056 --> 27:40.659
I mean, the theory
that Aaron killed Patrick

27:40.659 --> 27:43.028
because he didn't do his share
of the chores never made sense.

27:43.028 --> 27:44.897
For one thing,
they had a housekeeper.

27:44.897 --> 27:46.532
For another,
Aaron is not a psychopath,

27:46.532 --> 27:48.400
which you would have to be
to stab your roommate

27:48.400 --> 27:50.469
for leaving dirty dishes
in the sink.

27:50.469 --> 27:54.139
I mean, I've come close to
stabbing him over dirty dishes,

27:54.139 --> 27:56.708
but that's different --
we're married.

27:56.708 --> 27:57.809
Mm.

27:57.809 --> 27:58.977
Interviewer: What do you say
to the theory

27:58.977 --> 28:01.180
that Aaron had a falling out
with his roommate?

28:01.180 --> 28:03.982
Aaron and Patrick
were out partying that night.

28:03.982 --> 28:05.517
Does that sound like
a broken friendship

28:05.517 --> 28:07.019
careening towards murder?

28:07.019 --> 28:09.421
By his own admission, Aaron was
taking prescription drugs.

28:09.421 --> 28:12.357
Yeah. For a football injury
he got in high school.

28:12.357 --> 28:15.527
They impair your ability
to operate heavy machinery,

28:15.527 --> 28:18.530
not -- not turn you
into a hardened killer.

28:18.530 --> 28:19.698
♪♪

28:19.698 --> 28:22.000
Aaron passed out early.

28:22.000 --> 28:23.168
Woke up in the middle
of the night.

28:23.168 --> 28:26.838
Went to pee
and found Patrick's body.

28:26.838 --> 28:35.847
♪♪

28:35.847 --> 28:38.850
The French police took one look
at a young Black man,

28:38.850 --> 28:40.552
and decided he was the killer.

28:40.552 --> 28:43.055
I mean, they didn't even pursue
any other suspects.

28:43.055 --> 28:44.957
Bonjour, I appreciate you
speaking with me.

28:44.957 --> 28:47.259
[ Scoffs ] Your accent
is terrible.

28:47.259 --> 28:48.560
Um, Detective,
you've been accused

28:48.560 --> 28:51.063
of leading an incredibly biased
investigation --

28:51.063 --> 28:52.898
<i>Mais non.</i>
[ Speaks French ]

28:52.898 --> 28:54.266
We followed the facts.

28:54.266 --> 28:56.201
Mm. And the fact
that Patrick picked up

28:56.201 --> 28:57.769
a woman at the club
that night?

28:57.769 --> 28:59.037
Collette Lavinge?

28:59.037 --> 29:01.440
She was seen leaving
the apartment

29:01.440 --> 29:03.041
before the time of death.

29:03.041 --> 29:04.276
Understand?

29:04.276 --> 29:06.712
What about her jealous,
controlling boyfriend?

29:06.712 --> 29:08.046
Did you interview him?

29:10.048 --> 29:12.584
No. We did not.
Mm.

29:12.584 --> 29:13.986
Interviewer: But the thing that
ultimately got you released

29:13.986 --> 29:16.755
from prison was the
identification of this man.

29:16.755 --> 29:18.457
Aaron: Yeah.
Collette's boyfriend, Julien.

29:18.457 --> 29:20.759
Handsome. French.

29:20.759 --> 29:22.761
And, you know,
let's just say it --

29:22.761 --> 29:24.463
he's super white.
You know?

29:24.463 --> 29:25.964
Uh, what is --

29:25.964 --> 29:28.267
What is "Finance Bro"
in French?

29:28.267 --> 29:30.636
Shouldn't you know that?
You spent years in France.

29:30.636 --> 29:33.071
Yeah, but I didn't --
I didn't retain it.

29:33.071 --> 29:36.241
It was actually a group
of Internet sleuths

29:36.241 --> 29:37.809
who found
Collette's boyfriend.

29:37.809 --> 29:41.280
They spent countless hours
investigating Aaron's case.

29:41.280 --> 29:42.914
They also pointed
the finger at dozens

29:42.914 --> 29:44.616
of innocent people,
ruining their lives.

29:44.616 --> 29:47.786
Yes. Some members of the group
took it a little too far.

29:47.786 --> 29:50.455
Interviewer:
We've been looking at the
Internet sleuths, actually.

29:50.455 --> 29:54.359
Any chance you post under
the title "truecrimejunkie"?

29:55.460 --> 29:56.361
I...

29:57.796 --> 30:00.532
That -- That --
That doesn't s--

30:00.532 --> 30:03.001
I might have logged on once --
once or twice, yeah.

30:03.001 --> 30:04.603
Seriously?

30:04.603 --> 30:06.605
I mean, can you not see
how people would take that

30:06.605 --> 30:07.939
as a clear sign of bias?

30:07.939 --> 30:11.943
I categorically deny any
preferential treatment, okay?

30:11.943 --> 30:13.278
Interviewer: How can you say
that with a straight face,

30:13.278 --> 30:14.780
when it was revealed that Julien
was the son

30:14.780 --> 30:16.448
of the French
Finance Minister?

30:16.448 --> 30:18.116
Are you telling me you didn't
get a phone call asking you --

30:18.116 --> 30:18.950
[ Speaking French ]

30:18.950 --> 30:20.018
<i>Merci beaucoup.</i>

30:20.018 --> 30:21.486
<i>C'est terminé.</i>

30:21.486 --> 30:22.654
<i>Merci.</i>

30:22.654 --> 30:24.556
Oh, come on. Don't do that.
Come back.

30:24.556 --> 30:26.325
Interviewer: So, it must've been
so frustrating to learn

30:26.325 --> 30:27.993
that the French police
knew his identity

30:27.993 --> 30:30.829
before your first trial
and didn't say anything.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.331
I mean, yeah.
The -- The good news

30:32.331 --> 30:35.834
was that the fact
that they ignored Julien --

30:35.834 --> 30:37.803
uh, it got me my retrial.

30:37.803 --> 30:42.507
But the bad news was the
unidentified DNA on the knife --

30:42.507 --> 30:43.875
it -- it didn't belong
to Julien.

30:43.875 --> 30:46.311
So he --
You know, he had an alibi.

30:46.311 --> 30:47.546
As horrible
as the experience was,

30:47.546 --> 30:49.815
is there anything that you
actually miss from that time?

30:49.815 --> 30:51.316
I miss?

30:51.316 --> 30:52.517
God, no.

30:52.517 --> 30:54.386
W--

30:54.386 --> 30:56.054
Well, Carlos.

30:56.054 --> 30:57.089
Carlos?

30:57.089 --> 30:58.023
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

30:58.023 --> 31:00.192
Uh, Carlos the Jackal.

31:00.192 --> 31:01.760
He -- He was my cellmate.

31:01.760 --> 31:04.596
And, uh, man, pbht,
he has some stories.

31:04.596 --> 31:06.531
So you're saying the Jackal
got you through

31:06.531 --> 31:08.266
your year and a half
of incarceration?

31:08.266 --> 31:09.668
No.

31:09.668 --> 31:10.669
My mom did.

31:10.669 --> 31:12.170
Yeah, I don't --

31:12.170 --> 31:14.539
I don't think I would have got
through it without her.

31:14.539 --> 31:15.674
Um...

31:15.674 --> 31:19.511
She actually leased an apartment
in Paris

31:19.511 --> 31:20.846
until I was released.

31:20.846 --> 31:23.081
And, uh, she visited me
every week.

31:23.081 --> 31:25.016
And I'll tell you what.
If they would have let her,

31:25.016 --> 31:26.284
she would have been over there
every day.

31:26.284 --> 31:28.053
Of course I moved to Paris.

31:28.053 --> 31:29.287
I'm his mother.

31:29.287 --> 31:32.057
I would have served the prison
time for him if I could.

31:32.057 --> 31:33.225
You're a close family.

31:33.225 --> 31:34.226
We are.

31:34.226 --> 31:35.594
We've been tested.

31:35.594 --> 31:37.596
Were you close
with Patrick?

31:37.596 --> 31:38.730
Yes.

31:38.730 --> 31:39.965
I adored him.

31:39.965 --> 31:41.466
He was a wonderful boy.

31:41.466 --> 31:42.567
According
to your friends,

31:42.567 --> 31:43.702
you thought Patrick
was a troublemaker,

31:43.702 --> 31:45.036
and a bad influence
on Aaron.

31:45.036 --> 31:47.272
Anyone who said that
was lying.

31:47.272 --> 31:50.709
Yvonne -- were you in Paris
the day Patrick was murdered?

31:51.710 --> 31:54.579
Of course not.
I was here in LA.

31:54.579 --> 31:56.081
How do you explain
this footage,

31:56.081 --> 31:58.049
taken the day
of Patrick's murder?

31:58.049 --> 31:59.651
[ Vehicles passing ]

31:59.651 --> 32:06.091
♪♪

32:06.091 --> 32:07.426
Oh, hell, no.

32:07.426 --> 32:08.760
This interview is over.

32:08.760 --> 32:10.595
Yvonne.
No. No.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.764
We did not okay
this question.

32:12.764 --> 32:14.599
Who do you think you are?

32:14.599 --> 32:15.634
Fired!

32:15.634 --> 32:16.568
I actually don't work
for you.

32:16.568 --> 32:17.569
You need to kiss my ass.

32:21.606 --> 32:23.408
Interviewer: Did you know
that your mother was in Paris

32:23.408 --> 32:24.409
the day that
Patrick was killed?

32:24.409 --> 32:25.744
What?

32:25.744 --> 32:28.246
No, she was --
she was home in LA.

32:28.246 --> 32:29.948
Mm. We have footage
of her shopping

32:29.948 --> 32:32.017
on the Champs-Elysées
the night of the murder.

32:32.017 --> 32:34.686
Okay, well, that -- [ Chuckles ]
That's impossible.

32:34.686 --> 32:35.787
Isn't this her?

32:37.289 --> 32:42.828
♪♪

32:42.828 --> 32:45.664
[ Breathes deeply ]

32:45.664 --> 32:46.698
Okay.

32:48.467 --> 32:50.268
Officer Thorsen,
come back.

32:50.268 --> 32:52.604
Come on.
Let's finish this interview.

32:52.604 --> 32:54.606
Man: [ Whispering ]
Hey, there he is.

32:54.606 --> 32:56.007
Aaron: You lied to me.
Jimmy, get down.

32:56.007 --> 32:57.442
You lied to everyone.

32:57.442 --> 32:59.177
I didn't want all
my private business out there

32:59.177 --> 33:00.445
for all the world
to see.

33:00.445 --> 33:02.113
Mom, you are literally
producing

33:02.113 --> 33:03.615
a reality show
about our lives.

33:03.615 --> 33:05.150
That's different.

33:05.150 --> 33:07.352
I was on trial for murder,
fighting for my life.

33:07.352 --> 33:08.653
Exactly.

33:08.653 --> 33:11.156
The fact that I was even
in Paris on that night --

33:11.156 --> 33:12.324
how does that help you?

33:12.324 --> 33:13.325
Interviewer: And what was
your reaction

33:13.325 --> 33:14.659
to the revelation
that Aaron's mother

33:14.659 --> 33:16.194
was in Paris at the time
of the murder?

33:16.194 --> 33:17.863
Like, bombshell.
Game changer.

33:17.863 --> 33:20.398
I mean, none of this stuff came
out at the time of the trial.

33:20.398 --> 33:21.666
[ Chuckles ] This is --

33:21.666 --> 33:23.635
It's so exciting,
what it means for the case --

33:23.635 --> 33:26.037
Not for Aaron.
His mom lied to him.

33:26.037 --> 33:28.673
Y-Yes, that --
Well, that is true.

33:31.476 --> 33:32.978
Thanks for coming back in.

33:32.978 --> 33:34.212
We just need
to clear something up

33:34.212 --> 33:35.514
about the night Patrick
was killed.

33:35.514 --> 33:38.383
Patrick? I thought this was
about Morris's murder.

33:38.383 --> 33:40.352
Oh, it's about both.

33:40.352 --> 33:43.688
See, you felt Patrick
was a bad influence on your son.

33:43.688 --> 33:46.024
So you flew Aaron to Paris
to separate them.

33:46.024 --> 33:48.527
Only Patrick
followed Aaron there,

33:48.527 --> 33:50.595
so you took matters
into your own hands.

33:50.595 --> 33:52.864
You flew to Paris,
you killed Patrick.

33:52.864 --> 33:55.033
But somehow Morris
found out,

33:55.033 --> 33:57.502
so to keep
your deadly secret,

33:57.502 --> 33:59.004
you killed him too.

34:00.372 --> 34:03.842
Yeah,
that's a fun theory --

34:03.842 --> 34:06.378
a good story --
but you're wrong.

34:06.378 --> 34:08.179
Then explain
why you went to Paris

34:08.179 --> 34:10.015
and why you kept it
a secret.

34:10.015 --> 34:13.385
Because I was
with Jean-Pierre Darby.

34:13.385 --> 34:14.786
Who?
The footballer?

34:14.786 --> 34:18.390
Yes, we met a month before,
at a fashion show in Milan.

34:18.390 --> 34:19.558
I'm -- I'm sorry.

34:19.558 --> 34:22.227
You went to Paris for an
international bootie call?

34:22.227 --> 34:23.295
Yes.

34:23.295 --> 34:25.063
And we were in bed
all night.

34:25.063 --> 34:26.298
Ask him.

34:26.298 --> 34:28.733
Hell, ask the neighbors.

34:28.733 --> 34:31.036
Yvonne: They were determined
to convict you.

34:31.036 --> 34:33.038
Had it come out
that I was in town,

34:33.038 --> 34:34.539
they would've used it
against you,

34:34.539 --> 34:37.375
said that we were conspiring
to kill Patrick.

34:37.375 --> 34:40.445
Coming clean would've only hurt
your case, made it worse.

34:40.445 --> 34:42.948
Yeah, you know what? I forgot
how good you are at that.

34:42.948 --> 34:43.882
At what?

34:43.882 --> 34:45.750
At justifying yourself.

34:45.750 --> 34:48.753
You lied in a murder trial,
you cheated on your husband,

34:48.753 --> 34:51.089
and now you're the hero,
right?

34:51.089 --> 34:52.424
Yeah. Sure, Mom.

34:52.424 --> 34:53.658
We'll go with that.

34:57.429 --> 34:58.763
[ Sighs heavily ]

34:58.763 --> 35:00.465
Interviewer: You accused Aaron's
mother of the murder.

35:00.465 --> 35:02.334
With almost no evidence
to back it up.

35:02.334 --> 35:03.568
I -- I did.

35:03.568 --> 35:06.738
And, uh, in my defense,

35:06.738 --> 35:08.907
I'd been scrubbing
reality show footage

35:08.907 --> 35:10.942
for over 200 hours
at that point.

35:10.942 --> 35:12.444
So who broke the case?

35:12.444 --> 35:14.079
Oh, that was
Detective Lopez.

35:14.079 --> 35:15.914
My wife is a badass.

35:15.914 --> 35:17.582
We knew the murders
were connected.

35:17.582 --> 35:19.351
And we knew that
Patrick's murder in Paris

35:19.351 --> 35:20.819
was never
properly investigated.

35:20.819 --> 35:22.988
So I dug
back into that case.

35:22.988 --> 35:25.290
Right now I'm just trying
to build a timeline,

35:25.290 --> 35:27.792
getting to know more
about Patrick's life.

35:27.792 --> 35:30.128
What did the four of you do
that last month?

35:30.128 --> 35:31.630
No detail is too small.

35:31.630 --> 35:33.632
Um...

35:33.632 --> 35:36.167
Let's ask my brain.

35:36.167 --> 35:38.269
I can tell you one thing
that we definitely didn't do.

35:38.269 --> 35:39.604
Go to class.

35:39.604 --> 35:41.673
I mean, Aaron's parents
let him borrow their private jet

35:41.673 --> 35:43.942
anytime he wanted,
so we went all around Europe.

35:43.942 --> 35:46.611
I mean, Italy.

35:46.611 --> 35:47.612
Greece.

35:47.612 --> 35:48.446
French Riviera.

35:48.446 --> 35:49.481
[ Chuckles ]

35:49.481 --> 35:50.315
Can I see?

35:50.315 --> 35:51.683
Yeah.

35:51.683 --> 35:53.151
I thought --
screw school,

35:53.151 --> 35:55.487
when am I ever gonna get to
visit planet rich again, right?

35:55.487 --> 35:58.323
So, Santorini
for the weekend?

35:58.323 --> 35:59.491
Yes, please.

35:59.491 --> 36:01.159
These photos of you guys
on the tarmac,

36:01.159 --> 36:03.061
you always have
so much luggage.

36:03.061 --> 36:04.195
I know.

36:04.195 --> 36:06.898
Rowan always acted like
it was the Oregon Trail.

36:06.898 --> 36:08.400
Why?
Every time I've seen him,

36:08.400 --> 36:10.301
he was wearing a golf tee
and jeans.

36:10.301 --> 36:11.803
Not exactly
a clotheshorse.

36:11.803 --> 36:14.472
Oh, uh...

36:14.472 --> 36:15.373
True.

36:15.373 --> 36:16.875
I wonder
what was in there.

36:16.875 --> 36:19.310
Did you ever see Rowan
with drugs back then?

36:19.310 --> 36:20.512
I mean -- yeah.

36:20.512 --> 36:22.547
He was always kind of
"the life of the party,"

36:22.547 --> 36:23.648
if you know what I mean.

36:23.648 --> 36:25.216
Why?
Before Paris,

36:25.216 --> 36:27.686
Rowan's family in Iowa
was in financial trouble.

36:27.686 --> 36:29.020
He almost dropped
out of school.

36:29.020 --> 36:31.856
Now he lives in Brentwood
and drives a Porsche.

36:31.856 --> 36:33.525
I guess?

36:33.525 --> 36:36.061
I -- I see
you're very excited,

36:36.061 --> 36:38.697
and I love that --
I -- I'm not really following.

36:38.697 --> 36:39.764
I...

36:39.764 --> 36:40.699
[ Door closes ]

36:40.699 --> 36:42.233
Hey, Nolan.

36:42.233 --> 36:43.668
Where's Rowan?

36:43.668 --> 36:45.070
Uh, he just left.

36:45.070 --> 36:46.504
Why? I thought
you were done with him?

36:46.504 --> 36:48.707
I was -- until I realized
he's the one who killed Patrick.

36:52.577 --> 36:53.878
Alright. Here we go.
Here we go.

36:53.878 --> 36:55.246
Keith: Nice, nice.

36:55.246 --> 36:56.347
Bro, it's been crazy.

36:56.347 --> 36:57.749
I've added like
half a million followers

36:57.749 --> 36:59.217
from all the publicity.

36:59.217 --> 37:01.886
What? You think, uh --
You think, uh, Aaron did it?

37:01.886 --> 37:02.921
Pbht. Of course he did.

37:02.921 --> 37:04.556
The guy's a total psycho.

37:04.556 --> 37:05.724
Okay, watch this --

37:10.061 --> 37:11.563
Aw. Fudge.

37:11.563 --> 37:12.464
Hold on,
I'm gonna do it again --

37:12.464 --> 37:13.631
Okay, okay.
[ Siren chirping ]

37:13.631 --> 37:16.534
Rowan.
What the hell?

37:16.534 --> 37:18.036
We got a warrant
for your arrest.

37:18.036 --> 37:19.037
What?

37:19.037 --> 37:20.705
For what?

37:20.705 --> 37:23.441
Lucy: For the murders of
Patrick Hayes and Morris Mackey.

37:23.441 --> 37:24.542
Oh, snap.

37:24.542 --> 37:25.944
That's crazy.

37:25.944 --> 37:27.112
And wrong.

37:27.112 --> 37:29.047
I didn't --
why would you even think that?

37:29.047 --> 37:30.715
Because Patrick found out
you were smuggling drugs

37:30.715 --> 37:33.318
in Aaron's private jet, and
threatened to tell the police.

37:33.318 --> 37:35.587
Somehow Morris found out
that you killed Patrick

37:35.587 --> 37:37.756
to protect your secret,
so you killed him too.

37:37.756 --> 37:39.157
Come on.
That's -- I mean --

37:39.157 --> 37:40.258
That's so -- so wrong --

37:40.258 --> 37:41.926
-Hey! Rowan!
-Rowan!

37:41.926 --> 37:43.628
[ Siren wailing ]

37:43.628 --> 37:45.096
Okay.
Keith: Bro, wait.

37:45.096 --> 37:48.266
[ Siren wailing ]

37:48.266 --> 37:50.101
-Oh.
-Oh, snap.

37:54.072 --> 37:55.573
Lucy: You okay?

37:55.573 --> 37:57.242
Alright, you're fine.

37:57.242 --> 37:58.610
Stand up.

37:58.610 --> 38:00.278
Tim: Put it down.
You're under arrest.

38:00.278 --> 38:03.081
Rowan always had
these crazy plans.

38:03.081 --> 38:05.150
You know,
"Let's go to Morocco,"

38:05.150 --> 38:08.153
or, "Dude, I heard about
this sick party in Ibiza..."

38:08.153 --> 38:12.624
And I -- I --
I never thought about it,

38:12.624 --> 38:16.461
but he was the one who decided
where we were flying to always.

38:16.461 --> 38:18.696
And, you know,
now, looking back at it,

38:18.696 --> 38:22.801
with "cop eyes," I mean,
it is so obvious

38:22.801 --> 38:25.470
that Rowan
was up to something.

38:25.470 --> 38:27.105
I just could never see it.

38:28.807 --> 38:31.276
I mean,
Patrick did, though.

38:32.811 --> 38:35.847
But, like, why -- why --
why didn't he tell me, you know?

38:35.847 --> 38:38.283
We talked about everything --
you know, why wouldn't he --

38:38.283 --> 38:39.884
why wouldn't he tell me
about this?

38:42.053 --> 38:43.521
You know, if he had...

38:43.521 --> 38:46.658
♪♪

38:46.658 --> 38:48.159
everything --

38:48.159 --> 38:49.994
everything
would've been so different.

38:49.994 --> 38:55.500
♪♪

38:55.500 --> 38:56.668
[ Car alarm chirps ]

38:58.036 --> 38:59.137
Dexter: Aaron.

39:04.809 --> 39:06.811
Is it true?

39:06.811 --> 39:09.214
Yes, sir.

39:09.214 --> 39:12.150
Rowan Clauson confessed
to murdering Patrick.

39:15.353 --> 39:17.021
I'm so sorry
I didn't believe you.

39:19.691 --> 39:20.925
Can you ever forgive me?

39:23.595 --> 39:24.729
Of course.

39:27.031 --> 39:29.767
♪ Say you'll be there for me ♪

39:29.767 --> 39:33.338
After all this time, the case
of who killed Patrick Hayes

39:33.338 --> 39:35.006
was finally solved.

39:35.006 --> 39:37.041
But the question
that lingers is --

39:37.041 --> 39:40.211
is whether the emotional wounds
will heal --

39:40.211 --> 39:41.346
[ Inhales sharply ]

39:41.346 --> 39:42.213
♪ When I need you ♪

39:42.213 --> 39:44.048
Feels gross, right?
Yeah.

39:44.048 --> 39:46.384
♪ I need you ♪

39:46.384 --> 39:48.553
♪ Say you'll be there ♪

39:48.553 --> 39:49.787
Two people were dead.

39:49.787 --> 39:51.055
♪ ...for an answer that I... ♪

39:51.055 --> 39:53.558
Even after you catch the guy,
it's still just awful.

39:53.558 --> 39:55.894
♪ Look down and see the body
I can barely breathe in ♪

39:55.894 --> 39:58.396
I'm just glad
the truth finally came out.

39:58.396 --> 40:02.567
Aaron's innocence is now proven
without a doubt.

40:02.567 --> 40:05.203
He deserves to move on
with the rest of his life.

40:05.203 --> 40:07.906
And we'll be here
to help him do that.

40:07.906 --> 40:09.374
Interviewer:
And now that it's over,

40:09.374 --> 40:10.942
what's your view
of Aaron Thorsen?

40:10.942 --> 40:12.277
Ah. [ Chuckles ]

40:12.277 --> 40:15.747
I will admit, it took a minute
for Aaron to win me over.

40:15.747 --> 40:18.716
But once he did,
I knew he'd be a good cop.

40:18.716 --> 40:19.550
♪ I need your help ♪

40:19.550 --> 40:20.952
Alright, I'm done.

40:20.952 --> 40:22.420
Uh, wait.

40:22.420 --> 40:25.924
This is not gonna air before
his training is done, right?

40:25.924 --> 40:28.259
'Cause I gotta --
I gotta keep him hungry.

40:28.259 --> 40:31.596
I never once stopped
believing in my boy.

40:31.596 --> 40:33.932
Interviewer: Has he forgiven you
for the lie?

40:33.932 --> 40:35.600
He will.

40:35.600 --> 40:37.902
There's nothing our family
can't get through.

40:37.902 --> 40:39.470
It looks like Aaron
will finally be able

40:39.470 --> 40:40.772
to put all this behind him.

40:40.772 --> 40:43.241
That's -- That's not really
how it works.

40:43.241 --> 40:46.577
I mean, as someone
who has had friends killed,

40:46.577 --> 40:48.913
you never really
get closure.

40:48.913 --> 40:52.750
All you can hope for
is that the memories of them --

40:52.750 --> 40:55.687
the -- the good times
you had together --

40:55.687 --> 40:57.956
are what you see
when you think of them.

40:57.956 --> 40:59.958
How does it feel,
having the truth come out

40:59.958 --> 41:01.125
after all these years?

41:01.125 --> 41:02.961
♪ ...when I need you to ♪

41:02.961 --> 41:04.796
I-I-- I don't know.

41:04.796 --> 41:06.664
It's --
It's still sinking in.

41:06.664 --> 41:08.533
This is obviously gonna make
compelling episodes

41:08.533 --> 41:09.534
of your reality show.

41:09.534 --> 41:11.302
Oh, no. That --

41:11.302 --> 41:14.005
"Every Rose Has A Thorsen"
is not moving forward.

41:14.005 --> 41:16.174
I mean, it was --
it was a mistake to do

41:16.174 --> 41:18.009
in the first place, yeah.

41:18.009 --> 41:20.111
I mean, the only reason
why I did agree to it

41:20.111 --> 41:22.613
was to rehabilitate
my image.

41:22.613 --> 41:27.652
Um, but ironically it ended up
doing something even better --

41:27.652 --> 41:29.887
which was uncover the truth.

41:29.887 --> 41:32.156
So what
are you gonna do now?

41:32.156 --> 41:34.692
♪ You reach out and say
what I need to hear ♪

41:34.692 --> 41:38.863
♪ Might be dark right now
but the light is near ♪

41:38.863 --> 41:40.064
Live.

41:40.064 --> 41:42.700
♪ And I know that you... ♪
For myself.

41:42.700 --> 41:43.968
♪ ...will always be here ♪
And for Patrick.

41:43.968 --> 41:44.969
Mm-hmm.

41:53.478 --> 42:01.519
♪♪

42:01.519 --> 42:09.527
♪♪

42:09.527 --> 42:17.535
♪♪
